reviewText: I did a decent amount of research before buying this...untimatelty from amazon. What I wanted to know was:1. Was this 1.33:1 (full screen) or Widescreen (hopefully anamorphic)?2. Was it stereo or surround?I did find an answer. The wrong answer. A small number of websites (who actually had the information) said 1.33:1/stereo. Amazon even says 1.33:1. This is not 1.33:1. It is 1.85:1 anamorphic widescreen. While it does have stereo on the disc it also has 5.1 Surround, both Dolby Digital and DTS. Amazing presentation.DVD aside the preformance on the disc is awesome. It's obvious Julieta enjoys what she's doing. I've heard alot of music...I currently own hundreds of albums from all over the world and she is one of my favorites. I've heard very few artists who can time and time again deliver amazing preformances one after the other. Not only does she sing she writes songs, plays the accordion, produces, and arranges as well.

reviewText: All I say is WOW!!!  It was instant love.  This girl has the total package, period.  It was only recently that I've been into Latin Alternative, and this article I read mentioned that Julieta and Cafe Tacuba were the head of the pack.  So I took the splash and bought the combo CD/DVD of her MTV Unplugged performance, and I was flat-out stunned!!!She reminds me of a Latin Feist, Lenka or KT Tunstall, even Lily Allen, but with her own unique flavour.  I could not skip tracks or turn it off...I was transfixed.  I loved her childlike enthusiasm and her ability on various instruments, as well as that of her band (her drummer rocks), and even a guy on TUBA...you do NOT see that everyday.I loved the crowd's enthusiasm too, singing along to every song.  Julieta's performance made me an instant fan...now I have to buy all her studio albums, and collabos and see her live.  And I don't know that much Espanol...doesn't matter one iota.Now, if ever she does an album in Ingles, I have a feeling it will be interesting and not watered down either...that's how good she is.

reviewText: Julieta Venegas demuestra en este Unplugged que su musica tiene vigencia y fuerza aun traducida al formato Unplugged. Las canciones son presentadas con novedosos arreglos y ella y la banda dan una demostracion de profesionalismo y a lavez muestran lo mucho que se divierten al interpretar los temas. Muy recomendado como novedad o para conocer mas de esta impresionante artista.

reviewText: This dvd is a must buy for any Julieta Venegas fan! Even if you look at the list of songs and believe its just the same thing all over, think again! Because this DVD is unplugged you have Julieta experimenting with new beats, instruments, and introducing new guest artists that have influenced her musical career. The audio is amazing as well as her performance, you will enjoy this dvd.

reviewText: This a great selection of tracks. These songs aren't the same songs as the originals, using acoustic instruments, they're actually rearranged for this presentation. The duets are amazing, the best, in my opinion, being Ilusión with Marisa Monte. Also, see people who are normally not in videos, like Natalia Laforcade and Gustavo Santalaolla (who did soundtracks for the movies 21 grams, Amores Perros, Motorcycle diaries and Brokeback Mountain). Worth every penny. A real treat for fans.

reviewText: The albumI had always been reluctant to buy a Julieta Venegas' album, I don't think of her as a great lyricist nor a great musician. However, there's always something about her songs, they all have a catchy phrase or chorus that you will end up humming regardless if you like the song or not. Something I did admire is that she is an artist who likes to take risks, either by playing instruments you don't usually hear in a pop song or by making duets with the most unexpected artists; it seems to me she is authentic in her musical proposal.I recently had the chance to watch her Mtv Unplugged that aired on cable and I just loved it. The arrangements, the guest stars and her voice, this was indeed her best time and her moment to have an unplugged. The best thing is that the album has most of her hits and all of them with new arrangements, as well as a couple new songs.The single "El presente" is nothing but a taste of what the whole album delivers, there are many great songs in superb arrangements (either by Jacques Morelenbaum or Gustavo Santaolalla, her producer) highlights of the album would be the rearranged "Algo esta cambiando", "Seria feliz" (which sounds great unplugged), "Mirame bien", "Andar conmigo" and "illusion"Part of what makes this album so enjoyable are the guests, la "Mala" Rodriguez does great in her rendition of "Eres para mi" (even though the part she sings is from a Bajofondo song she collaborated in, not new material precisely), Santaolalla plays the banjo in "Algun dia", Juan Son (Porter) does ok in "De mis pasos", I don't know if it's just me (or the Bjork fan in me for that matter) but he feels forced and sings as if he were trying to emulate Bjork. The best of all is the incredible Marisa Monte, I had no idea she would be in this unplugged until I saw her standing there singing this beautiful song in Portuguese, to me that would be the song in the album.The DVDIt looks like the music industry is finally learning they need to present the new releases using the new formats. The DVD is presented in anamorphic widescreen format with stereo, 5.1 Surround. It simply looks and sounds incredible!While I know the new format is BD, I had always complained this type of material (unpluggeds, concerts etc) have always been released in standard TV formats, which don't look good on a widescreen HDTV, I have been surprised recently some companies are changing this.The tracklist is pretty much the same from the disc, with a "making of" documentary included. While Julieta seems nervous most of the times, she also seems to enjoy being on stage with friends and musicians she admires. The DVD opens with a piano version of "Lento" (not included in the CD), the rest of the concert only varies in the sense that it includes Julieta's comments in the middle of each song.A great unplugged and a pretty good presentation. Already looking forward to what she does next
summary: Finally a reason to become a fan

reviewText: Ever since her excellent first U.S. release, "Aquí," Julieta Venegas has done nothing but improve in every way. With each release, her song writing, arrangements, and delivery have matured, to the point where one wonders if it possible for her to get any better. With her most recent previous release, "Limon y Sal," Venegas proved that popular music (in any language) can actually be interesting as well as entertaining. When I first heard "Limon y Sal," I assume that she had reached a peak. Now "MTV Unplugged" brings together her best music in a superb live performance that surpasses everything she had previously produced. Her performance throughout is tight and disciplined with charm to spare. The assembled musicians are equally tight, surpassing the studio musicians of past CD releases. While the DVD contains a few more songs than the CD version of "MTV Unplugged," it doesn't hurt to have an audio version of this great concert for the car. And, while you're at it, get a copy of another great Julieta Venegas CD, "Sí." Thank you, Julieta, for making music that holds up!
summary: Is it possible for her to get any better?
Title: N/A
